1
00:00:00,340 --> 00:00:02,613
Tab 1
1
We waited a little until prayer time was over

2
00:00:04,527 --> 00:00:06,421
Before <i>maghreb</i> [sunset] prayer, they brought us out and said

3
00:00:07,262 --> 00:00:08,262
Everyone out

4
00:00:09,061 --> 00:00:10,449
A group of us were taken

5
00:00:11,023 --> 00:00:12,266
There were four or five of us, they took us out

6
00:00:12,300 --> 00:00:14,246
We came to this room

7
00:00:15,240 --> 00:00:16,445
There were other prisoners inside

8
00:00:18,026 --> 00:00:19,666
Each one sitting in a corner

9
00:00:20,013 --> 00:00:21,013
I came in

10
00:00:21,480 --> 00:00:23,705
And as you know, I wasn't familiar with any of this

11
00:00:24,786 --> 00:00:27,248
I was preoccupied thinking about what they would do to us

12
00:00:27,889 --> 00:00:30,247
No one knew what their fate would be

13
00:00:31,108 --> 00:00:33,909
I stood here, stayed for a quarter or half an hour

14
00:00:34,716 --> 00:00:37,032
And you're left powerless, helpless

15
00:00:37,973 --> 00:00:39,531
I stood here and sat down

16
00:00:40,232 --> 00:00:45,057
Interviewer: When they brought you out of the big hall where you prayed <i>asr</i> [afternoon]

17
00:00:45,643 --> 00:00:50,120
Was the placement into rooms optional?

18
00:00:50,165 --> 00:00:53,106
Could you choose any room, or were you placed wherever they wanted?

19
00:00:53,185 --> 00:00:54,865
No, no, it was as they wanted

20
00:00:55,205 --> 00:00:59,440
You go there, and you go there, and you go with those ones to that room

21
00:00:59,513 --> 00:01:01,010
Each person

22
00:01:01,604 --> 00:01:03,105
They started separating us

23
00:01:03,205 --> 00:01:04,980
You go there, and you go here

24
00:01:05,060 --> 00:01:06,775
Each one took a group and went upstairs

25
00:01:06,855 --> 00:01:09,950
Interviewer: Were the prisoners divided based on a list?

26
00:01:10,139 --> 00:01:14,219
Or were there no prisoner lists in the prison?

27
00:01:14,640 --> 00:01:16,670
I think there were lists

28
00:01:16,737 --> 00:01:19,354
Like lists of smokers, or of those who prayed—Come out here

29
00:01:19,434 --> 00:01:24,030
And those with other charges, or who’d tried to escape, or fought

30
00:01:24,903 --> 00:01:27,105
Each prisoner was placed according to his charge

31
00:01:27,401 --> 00:01:30,187
Interviewer: How many prisoners could this room hold?

32
00:01:30,327 --> 00:01:32,900
When I came in, there were about 20 people here

33
00:01:34,154 --> 00:01:36,027
We were in this room

34
00:01:36,394 --> 00:01:38,164
We were almost suffocating from how crowded it was

35
00:01:38,884 --> 00:01:41,892
And God forbid, if any bombing happened, none of us would survive

36
00:01:42,767 --> 00:01:44,718
Interviewer: Describe the state of the prisoners here

37
00:01:44,785 --> 00:01:48,678
How did you spend your first hour here?

38
00:01:49,396 --> 00:01:51,845
How did you spend your first night in this place?

39
00:01:53,977 --> 00:01:57,460
What did the prisoners talk about in this room?

40
00:01:57,696 --> 00:01:59,062
Were you free to speak?

41
00:01:59,122 --> 00:02:03,435
Or were you afraid of each other?

42
00:02:03,644 --> 00:02:06,274
The situation was miserable

43
00:02:06,407 --> 00:02:10,142
When you enter the room, everyone is carrying their own burden

44
00:02:11,076 --> 00:02:12,596
And they spend their time sleeping

45
00:02:14,031 --> 00:02:16,637
As for talking, of course we talked, like asking, What are your charges?

46
00:02:16,763 --> 00:02:19,697
Or where do you live, or are you related to someone, and so on

47
00:02:20,098 --> 00:02:21,432
But beyond that, you couldn't talk

48
00:02:21,492 --> 00:02:24,898
Because as the saying goes, the walls have ears

49
00:02:25,041 --> 00:02:28,411
You fear saying something and then paying the price for it

50
00:02:29,458 --> 00:02:35,312
Just normal talk—how were you detained, or why were you detained

51
00:02:36,043 --> 00:02:37,043
And such things

52
00:02:37,241 --> 00:02:39,880
Interviewer: When they first brought you in and took you into the hall

53
00:02:40,026 --> 00:02:43,143
Did you stay in the hall for three or four hours, until they brought you here?

54
00:02:43,609 --> 00:02:47,501
During that time, did they give you food or drinking water?

55
00:02:47,549 --> 00:02:49,903
During that time in the hall?

56
00:02:50,290 --> 00:02:51,644
In the hall, no

57
00:02:51,784 --> 00:02:53,325
Only at dinner time they would give us that

58
00:02:54,186 --> 00:02:57,696
They gave us rice and lentils

59
00:02:59,716 --> 00:03:01,525
Only that, and water

60
00:03:01,813 --> 00:03:05,276
Interviewer: The rice and lentils were served at dinner?

61
00:03:05,643 --> 00:03:09,959
Was it served in one big bowl for the whole group, or separately for each person?

62
00:03:10,773 --> 00:03:16,006
No, about four or five large bowls, they mixed the rice and lentils, and we ate

63
00:03:16,380 --> 00:03:18,521
Interviewer: So as a group?
Witness: Yes

64
00:03:18,961 --> 00:03:25,536
Interviewer: Okay, can you tell us about your psychological state?

65
00:03:25,662 --> 00:03:28,845
Your condition, or how you felt when you entered this room?

66
00:03:28,932 --> 00:03:33,296
What did you feel when you came to the same place today for the second time?

67
00:03:33,470 --> 00:03:35,753
Is it the same place?

68
00:03:35,907 --> 00:03:39,035
Did anything bring back memories, anything that happened here?

69
00:03:39,275 --> 00:03:43,212
The state you were in that night you spent in this place?

70
00:03:43,499 --> 00:03:46,961
A particular incident that happened to the prisoners or one of them?

71
00:03:47,075 --> 00:03:48,954
Something you can't forget and still remember?

72
00:03:49,277 --> 00:03:51,538
The situation was tragic, as I told you

73
00:03:51,637 --> 00:03:54,707
I mean, you were living with your family and sleeping

74
00:03:54,825 --> 00:03:58,171
Waking up in the morning and seeing your siblings, your father, and your wife

75
00:03:59,124 --> 00:04:02,374
You started thinking about how this night would pass

76
00:04:02,594 --> 00:04:04,755
You didn’t know how long you’d stay here, a night or two

77
00:04:04,983 --> 00:04:05,983
You didn’t know your fate

78
00:04:06,738 --> 00:04:11,747
There were small children among them, because of prayer, they would sit and cry

79
00:04:13,526 --> 00:04:15,563
They’d say to you, What did we do?

80
00:04:16,416 --> 00:04:19,982
That’s not even counting the fear of bombing

81
00:04:20,760 --> 00:04:23,999
It was a heartbreaking situation

82
00:04:24,746 --> 00:04:29,324
Interviewer: In this room, were there any video or surveillance cameras?

83
00:04:30,490 --> 00:04:31,781
No, I don’t think so

84
00:04:31,899 --> 00:04:34,642
There was only one direction

85
00:04:35,493 --> 00:04:39,104
You couldn’t focus on anything specific

86
00:04:39,720 --> 00:04:42,324
You just sat there in silence, doing nothing

87
00:04:42,784 --> 00:04:44,483
Interviewer: Do you mean a candle for lighting?

88
00:04:44,930 --> 00:04:45,947
Yes, a candle for lighting

89
00:04:46,234 --> 00:04:48,300
In a different prison there were cameras

90
00:04:49,580 --> 00:04:54,698
Interviewer: In this place, did you get to choose your spot to sit?

91
00:04:54,778 --> 00:04:58,447
Or were you not allowed to sit wherever you wanted?

92
00:04:58,528 --> 00:05:00,867
No, you and the prisoners

93
00:05:01,543 --> 00:05:03,557
Someone helps the other to secure a spot

94
00:05:04,085 --> 00:05:05,895
If your space was too small to sleep

95
00:05:06,508 --> 00:05:09,356
And someone else had a larger sleeping space

96
00:05:09,956 --> 00:05:13,502
He would sleep comfortably, then say to you, Go sleep over there

97
00:05:15,042 --> 00:05:19,523
Interviewer: On the first morning, when you first woke up

98
00:05:19,930 --> 00:05:24,633
How did you feel when you woke up and found yourself in the cell?

99
00:05:24,961 --> 00:05:28,269
Honestly, I was crying

100
00:05:29,803 --> 00:05:36,691
I pulled myself together, as you know there were young men sitting

101
00:05:38,381 --> 00:05:41,116
It was the first time something like this had happened to me

102
00:05:42,349 --> 00:05:45,728
I woke up in the morning in a strange place, I wasn’t with my family or my brothers

103
00:05:46,373 --> 00:05:47,373
It’s a feeling you can’t describe

104
00:05:47,828 --> 00:05:51,004
Interviewer: Was the reason for crying, fear or missing your family?

105
00:05:51,075 --> 00:05:52,096
No, missing my family

106
00:05:53,566 --> 00:05:56,756
There’s fear inside you

107
00:05:57,195 --> 00:06:01,390
You’re afraid something might happen while you’re far away from your family

108
00:06:03,084 --> 00:06:07,532
Interviewer: Do you remember an incident that happened to one of the prisoners here?

109
00:06:07,592 --> 00:06:08,592
Don’t you remember?

110
00:06:11,960 --> 00:06:12,960
No, there’s nothing

111
00:06:13,386 --> 00:06:17,351
Interviewer: Was there a clock hanging in that place?

112
00:06:17,815 --> 00:06:19,001
Was there a wall clock?

113
00:06:19,065 --> 00:06:20,082
No, there wasn’t a clock

114
00:06:20,134 --> 00:06:21,777
Interviewer: Wasn’t there anything else hanging on the wall?

115
00:06:22,622 --> 00:06:23,622
No, there was nothing

116
00:06:26,515 --> 00:06:29,034
Interviewer: Did the guards walk between the rooms or not?

117
00:06:29,885 --> 00:06:31,837
One of them stood in the corridor

118
00:06:32,507 --> 00:06:35,767
If you wanted to go to the toilet or ask for something

119
00:06:36,693 --> 00:06:37,966
You’d call him, he’d come and open the door for you

120
00:06:38,760 --> 00:06:40,656
Interviewer: And did you go out?

121
00:06:40,708 --> 00:06:41,714
No, I didn’t go out

122
00:06:42,387 --> 00:06:44,055
Interviewer: Was it for dawn prayer?

123
00:06:44,123 --> 00:06:45,370
Yes, I went out for dawn prayer

124
00:06:45,784 --> 00:06:48,739
At dinner time I’d go out to do <i>wudu</i> [ablution]

125
00:06:49,459 --> 00:06:51,482
Interviewer: How many toilets were there?

126
00:06:52,030 --> 00:06:53,030
Here

127
00:06:53,915 --> 00:06:55,035
And those toilets

128
00:06:55,884 --> 00:06:57,359
At dawn prayer, you have to wake up

129
00:06:58,570 --> 00:07:00,770
An hour before prayer, so you get time

130
00:07:01,913 --> 00:07:03,163
To get into the toilet
